-- Yankees-Tigers ALCS Game 4 Start Is Delayed by Rain in Detroit
-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 2012-10-18T00:16:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-18/yankees-tigers-alcs-game-4-start-is-delayed-by-rain-in-detroit.html
The start of Game 4 of the American
League Championship Series between the  New York  Yankees and
 Detroit Tigers  has been delayed by rain in Detroit.  The Tigers hold a three-games-to-none lead and can complete
a sweep of the best-of-seven Major League Baseball playoff
series with a victory tonight.  Game 3 of the National League Championship Series between
the St. Louis Cardinals and San Francisco Giants is also in a
rain delay. The Cardinals hold a 3-1 lead in the bottom of the
seventh inning in St. Louis.  The NLCS is tied at one game apiece.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Matuszewski in New York at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  